{"questionId":"35030655","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The materials for constructing the containers can be purchased at a discount according to the information in the table.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"height:159px;border-color:#000000;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" border=\"1\" width=\"516\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:250px;text-align:center;\">\n<strong>Cost of materials (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mo mathvariant=\"bold\">$</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">C</mi></math>)</strong><br><strong>before discount</strong>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:250px;text-align:center;\">\n<strong>Discount applied to</strong><br><strong>entire order</strong>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:250px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1000</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>2500</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:250px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>%</mo></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:250px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2500</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>5000</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:250px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>%</mo></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:250px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5000</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:250px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>%</mo></math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:250px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn></math></td>\n<td style=\"width:250px;text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>%</mo></math></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an exact expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>equating a volume of a half cylinder (or cylinder) to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>l</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not accept decimal approximation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math> for the <em><strong>A1</strong></em> given the demand of question.</p>\n<p>Condone the use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi></math> for the <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"35030655","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ1.5a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find an exact expression for l in terms of r and π.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—G